<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The thugs had stolen two camp chairs and a bag inside a parked car while the owner was in one of the shops. The thugs had run off and stopped a few streets away. They sat on the chairs while searching the bag. When the woman noticed that her car had been broken into, she cried out for help. A man who had been a victim of the same crime the day before contacted security guards, and they drove around the CBD looking for the suspects. As they made a turn in one of the streets, the woman noticed two men sitting on her chairs while going through her bag.When the suspects were approached, they fled but one of them was caught. Police were called and the suspect was arrested.A guard said: “We’ve had many complaints from people losing items in their cars but never knew who was behind it. Today we’ve managed to catch one of the culprits. and we will work with cops to stop this crime.”An automatic gate mobiliser was seized from the suspect, and a camp chair and the bag were recovered.Police are investigating cases of theft and possession of stolen property.